document_data.Geography:
{{Quote|To get to Zakhara, go south. Then go south some more.|Faerûnian saying}}
The land was located south and east of Faerûn, beyond the region of the [[Utter East]], with the closest Faerûnian lands to Zakhara being [[Dambrath]] and [[Var the Golden]] (by sea) and [[Ulgarth]] or arguably [[Konigheim]] (by land).<ref> Zakhara was mostly isolated from the rest of the world, as the peninsula was separated from the main mass by the treacherous [[World Pillar Mountains]].<ref> 

The [[Zakharan seas|seas around Zakhara]] were plagued with [[pirate]]s and [[Corsair (kit)|corsairs]] who charged traders tolls to cross their seas, such traders willingly paid these exorbitant fees as Zakhara's exotic trading goods tended to be well worth the price back in Faerûn. Occasionally the pirates decided to completely cut off Zakhara from Faerûn.
